# GitHub Copilot Workshop - December 2025

Welcome to the GitHub Copilot Workshop training materials repository! This repository contains comprehensive resources to help you master GitHub Copilot across different domains and skill levels.

## üìö Workshop Materials

This workshop includes the following training modules:

### 1. [Tips, Tricks and Best Practices for GitHub Copilot](./Tips%20Tricks%20and%20Best%20Practices%20for%20GitHub%20Copilot_v4.pdf)
Essential fundamentals and best practices to get started:
- Core concepts and basics
- Productivity tips
- Common use cases
- Troubleshooting common issues

### 2. [GitHub Copilot Developer](./GitHub%20Copilot%20Developer_v2.pdf)
Essential guide for developers getting started with GitHub Copilot:
- Setting up and configuring GitHub Copilot
- Core development workflows
- Writing code with AI assistance
- Practical coding examples and exercises

### 3. [GitHub Copilot DevOps](./Github%20Copilot%20DevOps_v3.pdf)
Leverage GitHub Copilot for DevOps practices:
- Infrastructure as Code (IaC) with Copilot
- CI/CD pipeline development
- Automation scripting
- Configuration management

### 4. [GitHub Copilot ML Data Ops](./Github%20Copilot%20ML%20Data%20Ops_v2.pdf)
Specialized training for ML and Data Operations:
- Machine learning workflows with Copilot
- Data processing and analysis
- Model development and training
- MLOps best practices

### 5. [Introduction to Prompt Engineering for GitHub Copilot](./Introduction%20to%20Prompt%20Engineering%20for%20GitHub%20Copilot_v4.pdf)
Advanced techniques for writing effective prompts:
- Advanced prompt engineering strategies
- How to communicate effectively with AI
- Techniques to improve code suggestions
- Complex patterns and optimization

## üéØ Workshop Objectives

By the end of this workshop, you will be able to:
- ‚úÖ Write effective prompts to generate high-quality code
- ‚úÖ Integrate GitHub Copilot into your daily development workflow
- ‚úÖ Use Copilot for DevOps automation and infrastructure management
- ‚úÖ Apply Copilot to ML/Data science projects
- ‚úÖ Maximize productivity with advanced tips and tricks

## üöÄ Getting Started

1. **Download the materials**: All PDF files are included in this repository
2. **Follow the sequence**: We recommend starting with prompt engineering basics
3. **Practice**: Apply what you learn in your own projects
4. **Experiment**: Try different approaches and see what works best for you

## üìñ Recommended Learning Path

```
1. Tips, Tricks and Best Practices (Fundamentals)
   ‚Üì
2. GitHub Copilot Developer
   ‚Üì
3. Choose your focus:
   - DevOps ‚Üí GitHub Copilot DevOps
   - ML/Data ‚Üí GitHub Copilot ML Data Ops
   ‚Üì
4. Introduction to Prompt Engineering (Advanced)
```

